  "notes": {
    "what_to_observe": [
      "Click Start on the IIS App Tier. In the agent log, the 8 ExecuteCommand dispatches arrive in 3 waves: 3 + 3 + 2. Watching markers/primary/iis-NNN.running appear with the same cadence.",
      "Try threshold_pct 75 with batch_size 3: after batch 1, 3/8 = 37.5% < 75 → batch gate waits up to start_timeout_seconds. After batch 2, 6/8 = 75% ≥ threshold → parent transitions to RUNNING and the gate releases the third batch immediately.",
      "Switch cluster_concurrency_mode to 'parallel' (or remove the field) to compare: all 8 markers appear simultaneously."
    ],
    "use_in_production": "On a real tier with 100-200 members, batch_size 5-10 keeps the load on shared deps (DB pool, auth provider, config service) bounded. Pair with a sane threshold_pct (e.g. 50%) so the gate releases as soon as the tier is 'good enough', not waiting for the last laggard."
  }
